HEADWORD: Poussette
<hw>Pous*sette"</hw> <pr>(p⟦oomac⟧*s⟦ecr⟧t")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F., pushpin, fr. <ets>pousser</ets> to push. See
<er>Push</er>.]</ety> <def>A movement, or part of a figure, in the
contradance.</def> <rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

